description._content: ID: 074452 Title: Orang-Outang, sive Homo Sylvestris Provenance: T. Bennett and D. Brown: London, 1699 Caption: Anatomical drawing Notes: An anatomical drawing. Image taken from Orang-Outang, sive Homo Sylvestris: or, the Anatomy of a Pygmie compared with that of a monkey, an ape, and a man. To which is added a Philological Essay concerning the Pygmies, the cynocephali, the satyrs, and sphinges of the ancients, etc. Originally published/produced in T. Bennett and D. Brown: London, 1699.
